1. Import the Orders_per_region.csv file into Power Query from the Datasets folder on the desktop
2. Filter the "Orders per Region" query to only have customers with more than one order in a particular region
3. Filter the ReportsTo column in the Employees query to exclude null values
4. Right join the Total Sales table with the Orders per Region table, using the CompanyName, RegionDescriptin, and Year column as the joining columns from both tables
5. Expand the new column to include # Orders. Make sure to uncheck "Use original column Name as prefix" sort the table by # Orders in descending order
